events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 33 points and Darius Garland added 24 in the dynamic Cleveland backcourt's return from injury absences, and the Cavaliers rolled past LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers 114-100 Sunday for their eighth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Mitchell lead Cavs past Lakers to 8th straight win

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet returned from injury with season highs of 30 points and 11 assists, Scottie Barnes had 19 points and 10 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors overcame the absence of leading scorer Pascal Siakam to beat the Chicago Bulls 113-104 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has 30 points and 11 assists as Raptors beat Bulls

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 28 points, Ja Morant added 23 points, nine rebounds and six assists, and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 103-97 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane's 28, Morant's good finish lead Grizzlies past Wizards

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 23 points, reserve Collin Sexton added 22 and the Utah Jazz beat the Los Angeles Clippers 110-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson, Sexton lead surging Jazz past Clippers, 110-102
